ccruncher.title: test05
ccruncher.description:
Description: ------------------------------- 1000 obligors 2 sectors Odds obligors (500) belongs to S1 and even obligors (500) belongs to S2 correlated defaults correl(S1,S1) = 16% (=0.4*0.4) correl(S1,S2) = 3.5% (=0.4*0.35*0.25) correl(S2,S2) = 12.25% (=0.35*0.35) 4 ratings (A, B, C, D) with 1-year default probs (5%, 10%, 20%, 100%) 12 months Each obligor has an asset with this profile: asset value at t=12 is 1 if obligor is alive and asset value at t=12 is 0 if obligor dead (default)
Expected Results: ------------------------------- Expected Loss = 334*5%+333*10%+333*20% = 116.6
Tip: Use CCBinf to check that simulated values comes from the given parameters. Disable antithetic and lhs modes before to proceed. Use the following template as input file:
# ------------------------------ begin CCBINF input file nfactors = [2] dprob = [0.05, 0.01, 0.02]
nobligors = [ > for i in $(seq 1 1000); do > echo "167, 166, 167, 167, 167, 166;" > done ]
ndefaults = [ > tail -n+2 data/test05/sector-rating.csv | head -n 1000 | sed "s/\.00,/,/g; s/\.00/;/" ]
//NU.init = [15] //W.init = [0.4, 0.35] //R.init = [0.25]
NU.param = [1.0] W.param = [0.01, 0.01] R.param = [0.01 Z.param = [0.1] S.param = [0.5]
NU.level = [0.234] W.level = [0.234, 0.234] R.level = [0.234] Z.level = [0.44] S.level = [0.44] # ------------------------------ end CCBINF input file
